Use Case: External program creates equation
Actor(s): External program
Purpose: External program uses the equation editor's exported CORBA
interface to construct an equation
-------------------------
Description: 

Equation editor provides an interface through CORBA, activated through 
the Object Activation Framework. External program activates the
equation editor object through OAF and invokes CORBA methods to
construct an equation.

Alternative courses:

1. External program creates a view embedded in a window of its own in
which the equation editor renders the equation.

-------------------------
Type: primary, system-oriented

Cross References: 
Use as a rendering engine in symbolic manipulator
Embedding into word processor documents
